<TITLE> Khaleda unveils shadow budget </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 07 (bdnews24.com)-- Opposition leader Khaleda Zia has presented a shadow budget for the financial year 2010-11. She proposed allocation of funds in different sectors to attain economic growth with a vision to lift the economy to mid level by year 2015. The two-time former prime minister presented her budget proposal at the Sheraton Hotel in the capital at 4pm on Monday before a gathering of economists, diplomats, educationists, businessmen, industrialists and media professionals. "There is a real danger that the economy will falter and collapse in the coming years. "Our politics is for the welfare of the people, and we do not wish to see them go through days of economic and social hardships," said Khaleda. This is for the first time that the opposition party came up with a shadow budget. Finance minister AMA Muhith is set to table the national budget on June 10. b
